<subSubSection id="6AF6F6DA2B41FFA0FFBEFF70FE5E9D2B" pageId="77" pageNumber="82" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="2253A5512B41FFA0FFBEFF70FF099FB5" blockId="77.[113,647,216,623]" box="[113,213,216,242]" pageId="77" pageNumber="82">REMARKS</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2253A5512B41FFA0FFBEFF5FFE5E9D2B" blockId="77.[113,647,216,623]" pageId="77" pageNumber="82">
According to the drawing by 
<bibRefCitation id="467DD8A02B41FFA0FE74FF5FFD8B9E57" author="BUTLER A. G." box="[443,599,247,274]" pageId="77" pageNumber="82" pagination="172 - 182" refId="ref38550" refString="BUTLER A. G. 1873. - Revision of the genera Zephronia and Sphaerotherium, with description of new species. Proceedings of the Scientific Meetings of the Zoological Society of London 4: 172 - 182, plate XIX." type="journal article" year="1873">Butler (1873)</bibRefCitation>
, the male of 
<taxonomicName id="E5ECDED22B41FFA0FF0AFEBFFE049E74" baseAuthorityName="Butler" baseAuthorityYear="1873" box="[197,472,279,305]" class="Diplopoda" family="Arthrosphaeridae" genus="Zoosphaerium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sphaerotheriida" pageId="77" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stigmaticum">
<emphasis id="109879432B41FFA0FF0AFEBFFE049E74" box="[197,472,279,305]" italics="true" pageId="77" pageNumber="82">Zoosphaerium stigmaticum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a sclerotized knob on the hind face of the anal shield. Such a feature is not present in any single Malagasy giant pill-millipede species recorded so far. Although Butler states in the first description the 
<typeStatus id="FD571BF32B41FFA0FF6FFE1EFF0E9E95" box="[160,210,438,464]" pageId="77" pageNumber="82">type</typeStatus>
locality as 
<collectingCountry id="5AFBE5C12B41FFA0FE94FE1DFE3A9E8A" box="[347,486,437,463]" name="Madagascar" pageId="77" pageNumber="82">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
, it is possible that 
<taxonomicName id="E5ECDED22B41FFA0FF6AFE7DFE1F9EAA" baseAuthorityName="Butler" baseAuthorityYear="1873" box="[165,451,469,495]" class="Diplopoda" family="Arthrosphaeridae" genus="Zoosphaerium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sphaerotheriida" pageId="77" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stigmaticum">
<emphasis id="109879432B41FFA0FF6AFE7DFE1F9EAA" box="[165,451,469,495]" italics="true" pageId="77" pageNumber="82">Zoosphaerium stigmaticum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may represent an Australian 
<taxonomicName id="E5ECDED22B41FFA0FF3EFE5DFE779D4A" authorityName="Brandt" authorityYear="1833" box="[241,427,501,527]" class="Diplopoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sphaerotheriida" pageId="77" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Sphaerotheriida</taxonomicName>
, the only group of giant pill-millipedes in which such a sclerotized knob is common. The only known 
<typeStatus id="FD571BF32B41FFA0FE23FD9DFDC79D0A" box="[492,539,565,591]" pageId="77" pageNumber="82">type</typeStatus>
specimen seems no longer to exist.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
